title: Gossip | Watch: Miley describes herself as an 'international phenomenon' on Fallon. Says Kanye is 'old'
text:
She was joking, of course. Kind of. She's also a "freakin' bunny doing an interview, and my skirt is yellow and so is my top." This is Miley doing an emotional rollercoaster of an interview with Jimmy Fallon - which is always a beautiful thing.
What everyone is more interested in this morning, however, involve her thoughts on on her future president: "Even Kanye's kind of old, compared to me, but he's about to be our future president, so I shouldn't say too much." It depends on what you mean by "old"...
In another portion of the interview, Morley opened up on hosting SNL's 40th show: ""It was kind of weird. I was sitting there and was 20 feet, 15 feet from Leonardo DiCaprio sitting there with his mom and he was hitting a vap pen, but it wasn't him that was making me nervous. I was feeling this emotion because there's like an etiquacy when we're there, you need to pass that shit, Leo, and he never did. So that was weird to me."
We'd say "Don't ever change, Miley," but that's never going to happen.
Via The Hollywood Reporter
